This paper discusses the privacy and security concerns related to cryptocurrencies, which are often discussed in the computer security (cs.CR) and cryptography (cs.CY) communities. The paper also discusses the use of Big Data and electronic transactions, which are relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI) communities. Finally, the paper discusses potential compromise approaches, which may involve distributed systems and network protocols, relevant to the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) community.
